The issue is that there are no coefficients to extract when there is only one record. That is, if ```y = 1``` and ```x= 2```, the code ```summary(lm(y~x))$coefficients[2, 4]``` will error out. You can instead do a check.

```
gmch_function2 &lt;-function(value, years)
{
  if (length(value) ==1){
    return(NA_real_)
  } else {
    return(1-summary(lm(value~years))$coefficients[2,4]) #p_value_coeff
  }
}

dt[, .(val = gmch_function2(value, years)), by = .(Name_of, varia)]
```
Note the OP function was modified to accept vectors as well.

